1 j. Have the child excused from school attendance for religious purposes; and
2 k. Participate in parent-teacher organizations and other school organizations.
3 6. This section does not:
4 a. Authorize or allow a parent to abuse or neglect a child as provided under
5 sections 14 - 09 - 22 and 14 - 09 - 22.1 ;
6 b. Apply to a parental action or decision that would end life;
7 c. Prohibit a court from issuing an order otherwise permitted by law; or
8 d. Prohibit a health care provider from providing medical care or other services to a
9 minor pursuant to the requirements of section 14 - 10 - 17.1, 14 - 10 - 18.1, 14 - 10 - 19 ,
10 or 14 - 10 - 20 .
11 7. An employee of the state or a political subdivision or other public institution, except for
12 law enforcement personnel, may not encourage or coerce a child to withhold
13 information from the child's parent and may not withhold information that is relevant to
14 the physical, emotional, or mental health of the child from a child's parent.
15 8. a. A parent claiming to be aggrieved by a violation of this section may assert that
16 violation as a :
17 (1) Claim in a judicial proceeding, if the parent has exhausted all other options
18 to resolve the offense through the normal channels offered by the state,
19 local government entity, political subdivision, or other political institution; or
20 (2) Defense in a judicial proceeding .
21 b. If on the prevailing side of the judicial proceeding, the parent is entitled to
22 appropriate relief, including costs and reasonable attorney's fees.
23 c. A school board shall indemnify and hold harmless all school personnel for any
24 violations of this section.
25 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 15.1-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
26 and enacted as follows:
27 Parental involvement in child's education.
28 1. As used in this section, a "parent" means parent or legal guardian of a student of a
29 public school within the school district. The term does not include a school or other
30 institution serving in loco parentis.
31 2. The board of each school district shall:
